            <div type="prose">
                <head type="title"><hi rend="caps">LILLE</hi></head>   
                <p>Passeport, Monsieur, s'il vows plait&#x2014;. I hate:<lb/>
                    fortified towns, in genera, that is. &#x2014; There&#x2014;<lb/>
                    houss, are like barracks, their public buildings<lb/>
                    like prisions, their population, like so many rats<lb/>
                    in a rat trap, they are arduous to get in, dif&#x2013;<lb/>
                    ficult to get out, and disagreeable to remain in.<lb/>
                    To all this however, Lille is an exception, except in<lb/>
                    one circumstance, its difficulty of access.&#x2014; We were<lb/>
                    detained, after a long days journey, under a bur<lb/>
                    ning sun, hot, hungery, and stupid, while our<lb/>
                    passport was examined. Slowly the sentinel<lb/>
                    unfolded the paper, spelled over its contents with<lb/>
                    tiersome coolness, and provoking minuteness<lb/>
                    slowly returned it, and then came&#x2014; Passez. <!-- Unsure of the final word on this line-->
                    And pass we did, right gladly.&#x2014;. Lille is a<lb/>
                    
                </p>
                       
